The paper proposes a new algorithm for policy optimization in deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm involves regularization of the state-action visitation distribution, which is a common technique in optimization and control theory (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of off-policy data, which is a common topic in reinforcement learning (cs.AI). The proposed algorithm is evaluated on high-dimensional control tasks, which are often studied in robotics and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses deep neural networks to represent the policy, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV).
